body:
I'm in the alpha client and I wanted to ask about something, but when I tried to click on the "create a discussion" for the alpha discussion it stated "Must be level 12 or higher. The thing is I signed in to the league of legends website and my alpha client with my level 30, sliver 2 account. So why can't I create a discussion? 

If you wouldn't mind answering my alpha question (I'll type this just in case you'll be able to answer it); 

So the link provided stated that "We've also delayed the ability to purchase RP in the store. Otherwise, the store works fine, but you'll need to use the legacy client to stock up on our fake internet money." I was wondering where can I get the fake internet money? Thing is I don't know what the legacy client is, so what is it? Does fake internet money mean free RP? Also, does using my sliver 2 account effect anything with getting the fake internet money? Do I need to create a new account to get the free internet money?
